{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"You must exercise the real loader path across manifest parsing + module loading boundaries and verify that invalid-manifest plugins are never imported. A unit test of only validation logic can miss regressions where the loader imports the plugin before/while validating.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory containing an invalid `manifest.json` and an entry module with a visible side effect (e.g., writes a marker file/global flag on import). Run the real loader against that directory. Assert: (1) loader reports manifest validation failure, and (2) import side effect never occurred.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure risk is in dependency-graph resolution wired to lifecycle execution order. Mocking either piece can hide ordering bugs at module boundaries; this needs multiple real plugin manifests/modules loaded together.","test_description":"Create temp plugins `A` and `B` where `A` depends on `B`. Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-process log/file. Run loader and assert observed order is `B` then `A`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection must be verified in the full graph-construction + load pipeline, including the 'do not load either plugin' effect. Pure algorithm unit tests can miss integration bugs where detection is ignored or partial loading still happens.","test_description":"Create plugins `A` and `B` with mutual dependencies. Give each entry/onLoad a side effect marker. Run loader and assert: (1) cycle error is reported with both plugin names, and (2) neither entry side effect nor `onLoad` side effect occurred.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is about sequencing across real module import execution and lifecycle invocation. In-process mocks of imports can always pass while missing true Node module execution order/side effects.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginReady = true` on import and whose `onLoad` throws if that flag is not set. Run loader and assert `onLoad` succeeds and observes the flag, proving import execution happened first.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"You need real graph-aware initialization flow with failure handling across multiple plugins. Unit-testing an error handler or topological sort alone can miss regressions in continuation/skip behavior.","test_description":"Create plugins: `Failing` (throws in `onLoad`), `Independent` (no dependency), and `Dependent` (depends on `Failing`). Run loader and assert: (1) error for `Failing` is reported, (2) `Independent.onLoad` is still called, and (3) `Dependent.onLoad` is not called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
